comments.body:
Nit: I find it a bit unintuitive to use a loop variable inside the condition here, and would prefer:

```c++
LIMITED_WHILE(fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeBool(), NUM_ITERS) {
    if (iter >= NUM_ITERS) break;
    ...
```

